compact CET4 TEM4

形容词和名词读作 ˈkɒmpækt 。动词读作 kəmˈpækt 。 

1. ADJ Compact things are small or take up very little space. You use this word when you think this is a good quality. 小巧的 [表赞许] 

例： ...my compact office in Washington. …我在华盛顿的小巧办公室。 

2. ADJ A compact person is small but looks strong. 矮小结实的 

例： He was compact, probably no taller than me. 他矮小结实，大概没我高。 

3. N-COUNT A compact or a compact car is a car that is smaller than the average car, and that is economical to run. 小型汽车 

4. N-COUNT a small flat case containing a mirror, face powder, etc, designed to be carried in a woman's handbag 化妆盒 

5. N an official contract or agreement 官方合同; 官方协议 

6. V to pack or join closely together; compress; condense 紧密地装、连在一起; 压缩; 浓缩

</div>

